The paper focuses on refactoring activities in software maintenance, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of design-related metrics and anti-pattern enhancement changes suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and software design (cs.SD). The empirical analysis of the impact of refactoring on quality metrics suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
